<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Should Actually Buy</h2>

  <p>
    For most seed-starting shelves, choose a small clip-on fan with adjustable angle and low-speed settings. Mount it to the side of your shelf and aim it across the seedlings rather than directly at them.
  </p>

  <p>
    Avoid high-powered fans or complicated setups. A simple, well-placed fan will provide all the airflow most seedlings need.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Gentle airflow in the right direction matters more than fan strength.
  </p>
